targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'passed')) as pass
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'passed') = 'true'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'failed')) as fail
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'failed') = 'true'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'passed')) as pass
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'passed') = 'true'
AND platform = 'Android'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'failed')) as fail
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'failed') = 'true'
AND platform = 'Android'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'passed')) as pass
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'passed') = 'true'
AND platform = 'IOS'

SELECT
  now() as time,
  count((tr.info ->> 'failed')) as fail
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE (tr.info ->> 'failed') = 'true'
AND platform = 'IOS'

SELECT test_id
FROM test_id
ORDER BY timestamp DESC
LIMIT 1;

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'Android'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'passed'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'Android'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'failed'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  platform,
  test_id,
  (tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
  ROUND((tr.info ->> 'duration')::FLOAT) duration
FROM test_id ti
JOIN test_results tr ON (tr.info ->> 'test_id') = ti.test_id
WHERE platform = 'IOS'
AND info ->> 'outcome' = 'failed'
ORDER BY 1

SELECT ti.platform,
pr.info ->> 'run_id' as run_id,
(tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
tr.info ->> 'outcome' as outcome,
(elem ->> 'properties') as properties
-- keys.*,
FROM proxy_request pr
JOIN test_results tr on tr.info ->> 'test_id' = pr.info ->> 'run_id'
JOIN test_id ti on ti.test_id = pr.info ->> 'run_id'
CROSS JOIN json_array_elements(pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch') elem -- , json_object_keys(elem #> '{properties}') AS keys (mykey)
WHERE pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch' IS NOT NULL
AND elem -> 'properties' IS NOT NULL

SELECT ti.platform,
pr.info ->> 'run_id' as run_id,
(tr.info ->> 'node_id') as test,
tr.info ->> 'outcome' as outcome,
pr.info -> 'content' ->> 'batch' as batched_data
-- keys.*,
FROM proxy_request pr
JOIN test_results tr on tr.info ->> 'test_id' = pr.info ->> 'run_id'
JOIN test_id ti on ti.test_id = pr.info ->> 'run_id'
WHERE pr.info -> 'content' -> 'batch' IS NOT NULL

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info ->> 'run_id' as run_id,
  info ->> 'timestamp' as request_timestamp,
  info ->> 'host' as host,
  info ->> 'port' as port,
  info ->> 'method' as method,
  info ->> 'schema' as schema,
  info ->> 'authority' as authority,
  info ->> 'path' as path,
  info ->> 'http_version' as http_version,
  info ->> 'headers' as headers,
  info ->> 'content' as content,
  info ->> 'trailers' as trailers,
  info ->> 'timestamp_start' as timestamp_start,
  info ->> 'timestamp_end' as timestamp_end
FROM proxy_request
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info ->> 'run_id' as run_id,
  info ->> 'timestamp' as request_timestamp,
  info ->> 'http_version' as http_version,
  info ->> 'status_code' as status_code,
  info ->> 'reason' as reason,
  info ->> 'headers' as headers,
  info ->> 'content' as content,
  info ->> 'trailers' as trailers,
  info ->> 'timestamp_start' as timestamp_start,
  info ->> 'timestamp_end' as timestamp_end
FROM proxy_response
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info
FROM proxy_request
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1

SELECT
  "timestamp" AS "time",
  info
FROM proxy_response
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("timestamp")
ORDER BY 1
